<tool id="fimo_text_to_gffs" name="split fimo txt to gff files per motif" version="1.0.0">
    <description></description>
    <macros>
    </macros>
    <command> 
        <![CDATA[
        python $__tool_directory__/fimo_txt_2_gffs.py
	 --input "$input"

]]>
    </command>
    <inputs>
        <param name="input" type="data" format= "txt" label="fimo txt output file as input" />
    </inputs>

    <outputs>
        <collection name="output_gff" type="list" label=" ${tool.name} gff on ${on_string} ">
            <discover_datasets pattern="(?P&lt;designation&gt;.+)\.gff" directory="."  format= "gff" visible="false"  /> 
        </collection>
    </outputs>
    <tests>
    </tests>
    <help>
**What it does**
fimo default type is gff, so splitting fimo output leads to gff format file.

    </help>
</tool>

